Growing singly in soil near Tilia americana, Carpinus caroliniana, Quercus sect. Lobatae, Acer sp. and Rhododendron sp. Cap smooth, dry and innately fibrillose; 13.0 mm wide and 5.4 mm tall. Gills white and uncinate. Stem smooth; dry; tapering slightly toward the base; basal mycelium white; 28.3 mm long and 2.9 mm wide. Odor not distinctive. Pileipellis a cutis. Clamps lacking lamellar structures and pileipellis. Lamellar trama and basidia containing dextrinoid granules; appearing dextrinoid in mass. Lamellar cystidia absent. Basidia 2-sterigmate. Spores imamyloid, smooth and thin-walled. Spore measurements: (3.7) 3.8 – 4.8 (4.9) × (2.8) 3 – 3.8 (4.2) µm; Q = (1) 1.1 – 1.4 (1.7); N = 30; Me = 4.2 × 3.3 µm; Qe = 1.3
